Sales of Multi-Million Pound London Houses Rise, Times Reports

-- B y   N a n d i n i   S u k u m a r
-- 
2011-04-23T15:08:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-23/sales-of-multi-million-pound-london-houses-rise-times-reports.html
The number of homes sold in  London 
for more than 2 million pounds ($3.3 million) rose 60 percent
from 2008-2010, the  Times  reported, citing research from
Investec Specialist  Private Bank .  The London borough of Kensington and Chelsea reported 378
houses changing hands in that price category, the Times said.
Last year, the average price of a detached house in the area
exceeded 8 million pounds, a 54 percent increase compared with
2008, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nandini Sukumar in London at 
 nsukumar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
